HEADWORD: Disgarnish
<hw>Dis*gar"nish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>dis-</ets> + <ets>garnish</ets>. See <er>Degarnish</er>.]</ety>
<def>To divest of garniture; to disfurnish; to dismantle.</def>
<rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
